<paragraph blockId="85.[151,1436,892,1086]" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[208,336,934,960]" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Body fusiform; scapular setae (
<emphasis box="[711,735,935,960]" italics="true" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">sc</emphasis>
) and tubercles near rear shield margin, directed posteriorly; empodium entire; coxae I and coxae II each with 3 setae; opisthosoma with 3 ridges.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="85.[151,1436,892,1086]" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">
This genus consists of 52 species (
<bibRefCitation author="Amrine, J. W. Jr. &amp; Stasny, T. A. &amp; Flechtmann, C. H. W." box="[646,891,1018,1044]" pageId="85" pageNumber="86" refId="ref44790" refString="Amrine, J. W. Jr., Stasny, T. A. &amp; Flechtmann, C. H. W. (2003) Revised keys to world genera of Eriophyoidea (Acari: Prostigmata). Indira Publishing House, Michigan, U. S. A., 244 pp." type="book" year="2003">
Amrine 
<emphasis box="[750,808,1018,1043]" italics="true" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">et al</emphasis>
. 2003
</bibRefCitation>
). Only 2 of these have been recorded from Southeast Asia.
</paragraph>
